The paper deals with privacy concerns in scientific workflow systems, which involve storing and sharing data and module executions. This suggests a focus on data management (cs.DB) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The problem of minimizing the cost of hidden data also involves optimization and algorithms (cs.DS), while the use of provenance information and workflow modeling may relate to machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE).
